The recombinant baculovirus was generated after transfection of Sf9 cells with recombinant bacmid, which was named Bac-P12A3C. The titers of recombinant virus were measured at 1 × 108–1.3 × 108 plaque forming units/ml at the third passage. HF cells were then infected with recombinant baculovirus at an MOI of 10. Cells and supernatants were harvested and analyzed at 3 dpi, at which point most of the cells showed cytopathic effects. In the IFA, the recombinant virus-infected cells (but not the mock-infected cells) reacted with the rabbit anti-FMDV sera (Fig. 2
). The expressed proteins also reacted with sera against FMDV as shown by Western blotting, and four bands of approximately 24, 33, 47 and 81 kDa were detected. These results demonstrated that recombinant P1-2A (81 kDa) polyprotein was partially processed by 3C protease into VP31 (47 kDa), VP0 (33 kDa), VP3 (24 kDa) and VP1 (24 kDa) (Fig. 3
).
